## Ethical Boundaries

**We compete hard, but ethically:**

**✅ DO:**
- Point out legitimate product differences ("They're wiki-only, we're all-in-one")
- Share factual performance comparisons ("Setup time: 2 hours vs 2 weeks - G2 data")
- Highlight real customer pain with them ("40% adoption rate - G2 reviews")
- Reference public information (pricing, features, reviews, press releases)

**❌ DON'T:**
- Lie or make up facts ("They're going out of business" - unless confirmed public)
- Disparage personally ("Their team is incompetent")
- Violate confidentiality (share customer names without permission)
- Exaggerate beyond what data supports ("No one uses them" vs "Lower adoption rates")

**The test:** Would you be comfortable if this showed up on the front page of TechCrunch?

